hwDHCPServerMib.name: hwDHCPServerMib
hwDHCPServerMib.contactinfo: Platform Team Huawei 3Com Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
hwDHCPServerMib.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing DHCP server.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: To descript the status of some function is Enabled or Disabled.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global pools.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configurations of dhcp server global pools.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork, hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, or hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 1.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 2.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 3.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP global pools.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP global pools.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip ip at a time.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of gateway router.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of DNS server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of NetBios server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1st to 16th hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString.description: Ip string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hwDHCPSInterfacePoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hwDHCPSInterfacePoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hwDHCPSInterfacePoolLeaseUnlimited
hwDHCPSInterfacePoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

hwDHCPSInterfacePoolClientDNSIPString.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.
